==English==

===Etymology===
From the physics concept of "[[at infinity]]" or "far", where fields are small, and the math concept of [[null set]].  Ironically, a null infinity may be neither far nor a null set.

===Noun===
{{en-noun|sg=[[null]] [[infinity]]|pl=[[null infinities]]}}

# In a [[closed]] [[space-time]], especially for an [[Einstein cylinder]], null infinity is the limit of convergence of the [[light cone]].  That is, it is the limit of a set of points that each have a [[time-like]] [[separation]] from every point that has a [[space-like]] [[separation]] from a given point.

